Description: Fix CVE-2026-48959 - algorithmic-complexity DoS in IO::Uncompress::Unzip::fastForward
 IO::Uncompress::Unzip versions before 2.220 contain a typo in the
 fastForward() chunk-size clamp: the code applies Perl's length() operator
 to the integer $offset, which stringifies it and yields its digit count
 (1-19) rather than the offset value itself. The comparison
 "length $offset < $c" therefore evaluates to true on every iteration of
 the loop, collapsing the per-iteration read from 16 KiB down to 1-19
 bytes. When a named entry is extracted from an attacker-controlled zip
 archive via IO::Uncompress::Unzip->new($zip, Name => $target), the loop
 scales linearly with the entry's compressed size (up to ~4 GiB for
 non-Zip64 archives), causing CPU exhaustion / DoS (CWE-407).
 .
 The fix removes the spurious length() calls so the chunk-size clamp
 compares the remaining offset to the current chunk size, preserving the
 intended 16 KiB chunk reads and only shrinking the chunk on the loop's
 tail iteration.
 .
 This patch is the verbatim upstream IO-Compress 2.220 fix
 (commit 68db44076f4c1a86a2ffe53a958eac6cabaf72e2) backported to the
 IO-Compress 2.093 copy bundled in perl 5.32.1. The surrounding code in
 fastForward() is byte-identical between 2.093 and 2.220, so no
 contextual adjustment is required.
Origin: backport, https://github.com/pmqs/IO-Compress/commit/68db44076f4c1a86a2ffe53a958eac6cabaf72e2
Bug: https://github.com/pmqs/IO-Compress/issues/72
Bug-Debian: https://bugs.debian.org/1138856
Forwarded: not-needed
Author: Root.io Novel Patcher <security@root.io>
Last-Update: 2026-06-10

--- a/cpan/IO-Compress/lib/IO/Uncompress/Unzip.pm
+++ b/cpan/IO-Compress/lib/IO/Uncompress/Unzip.pm
@@ -144,8 +144,8 @@
 
     while ($offset > 0)
     {
-        $c = length $offset
-            if length $offset < $c ;
+        $c = $offset
+            if $offset < $c ;
 
         $offset -= $c;
 
Description: CVE-2026-42496 - Validate symlink linkname in SECURE MODE
 Archive::Tar did not validate the linkname of symlink entries
 when extracting in the default SECURE EXTRACT MODE. A crafted tar archive
 could create symlinks with absolute paths or paths containing ".."
 components, allowing extraction outside the target directory.
 .
 This patch rejects symlink entries whose linkname is absolute or
 contains ".." path components when running in SECURE EXTRACT MODE
 (i.e. when $INSECURE_EXTRACT_MODE is false). It also
 updates t/04_resolved_issues.t to set $INSECURE_EXTRACT_MODE=1 for the
 two pre-existing test cases that intentionally use a "../"-style
 linkname, so the existing tests continue to pass.
 .
 Backported from upstream Archive::Tar commit
 17c873492a05eddc0de18c1485e0b2cccd5a9158 (released in Archive::Tar 3.08).
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/jib/archive-tar-new/commit/17c873492a05eddc0de18c1485e0b2cccd5a9158
Author: Stig Palmquist <stig@stig.io>
Last-Update: 2026-05-27
---
--- a/cpan/Archive-Tar/lib/Archive/Tar.pm
+++ b/cpan/Archive-Tar/lib/Archive/Tar.pm
@@ -944,6 +944,19 @@ sub _make_special_file {
     my $err;

     if( $entry->is_symlink ) {
+        if( !$INSECURE_EXTRACT_MODE ) {
+            my $linkname = $entry->linkname;
+            if( File::Spec->file_name_is_absolute($linkname) ) {
+                $self->_error( qq[Symlink '] . $entry->full_path .
+                    qq[' has absolute target. Not extracting under SECURE EXTRACT MODE] );
+                return;
+            }
+            if( grep { $_ eq '..' } File::Spec->splitdir($linkname) ) {
+                $self->_error( qq[Symlink '] . $entry->full_path .
+                    qq[' target attempts traversal. Not extracting under SECURE EXTRACT MODE] );
+                return;
+            }
+        }
         my $fail;
         if( ON_UNIX ) {
             symlink( $entry->linkname, $file ) or $fail++;
