Description: CVE-2026-48962 - Remove use of eval in IO::Compress File::GlobMapper
 _parseOutputGlob wrapped a caller-controlled output pattern in double quotes
 and _getFiles passed the wrapped string to eval(), allowing an attacker who
 controls the output glob to execute arbitrary Perl code. This backports
 upstream commit f2db247b which replaces the eval-based substitution with
 safe sentinel-delimited string replacement.
 .
 Path remap: upstream paths lib/File/GlobMapper.pm and t/globmapper.t are
 shipped inside the Debian perl source tree under cpan/IO-Compress/.
 .
 Test hunk #1 context line adapted: target ships
 "import Test::NoWarnings;" while upstream had been refactored to
 "Test::NoWarnings->import;". The actual change (plan tests => 68 -> 76) is
 unchanged.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/pmqs/IO-Compress/commit/f2db247bf90d4cc7ee2710be384946081f3b4610
